{"lemma":"خَبِيثاتٌ","slug":"خَبِيثاتٌ","root":"خ.ب.ث","root_slug":"خ-ب-ث","root_link":"/words/roots/خ-ب-ث","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"خَبِيث","root":"خبث","pos":"N","occurrence_count":9},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n9874","n9877"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AE%D9%8E%D8%A8%D9%90%D9%8A%D8%AB%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"evil, wicked, malignant","examples":[{"text":"قُل لَّا يَسْتَوِي ٱلْخَبِيثُ وَٱلطَّيِّبُ وَلَوْ أَعْجَبَكَ كَثْرَةُ ٱلْخَبِيثِ ۚ فَٱتَّقُوا ٱللَّهَ يَا أُولِي ٱلْأَلْبَابِ لَعَلَّكُمْ تُفْلِحُونَ"},{"text":"الْخَبِيثَاتُ لِلْخَبِيثِينَ وَٱلْخَبِيثُونَ لِلْخَبِيثَاتِ وَٱلطَّيِّبَاتُ لِلطَّيِّبِينَ وَٱلطَّيِّبُونَ لِلطَّيِّبَاتِ أُولَٰئِكَ مُبَرَّءُونَ مِمَّا يَقُولُونَ لَهُمْ مَغْفِرَةٌ وَرِزْقٌ كَرِيمٌ"}]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/xa.biːθ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n9874","headword_ar":"خَبِيثٌ","root":"xbv","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"contr. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tay~ibN","text_ar":"طَيِّبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, Mgh, Msb, K;) applied to objects of the senses and to those of the intellect; (Kull p. 177;) to sustenance, or victuals, and to offspring, and men, and to other things: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Bad; corrupt:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disapproved, hated,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abominable;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA;) this accord. to IAar, being its primary signification: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"so in respect of taste,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of odour:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nasty, nauseous, loathsome,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disgusting:"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impure, unclean, foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filthy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb, TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unlawful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, Msb;) applied in this sense to certain food: and, applied to certain beverage,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"injurious:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) applied to medicine such as is forbidden in a certain trad., it means either"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impure and unlawful,"},{"kind":"text","text":"such as wine &c., or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nauseous to the taste:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, TA:) you say that a thing is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyv","text_ar":"خَبِيث"},{"kind":"text","text":"in taste, [and in odour,] and in colour: and you apply this epithet to adultery, or fornication; and to property unlawfully acquired; and to blood, and to the like things which God has forbidden: (TA:) also to such things as garlic and onions (Msb, TA) and leeks, (TA,) which are disagreeable in taste and odour: (TA:) and to such things as the serpent and the scorpion: (Msb:) applied to language, it means (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opprobrious,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a reviling nature;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA;) and (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupt"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of authority;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a bad dialect"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (A, TA:) applied to religion, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"infidel,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the nature of infidelity:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) applied to a man,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad, corrupt, base,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"abominable; wicked, deceitful, guileful, artful, crafty,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cunning;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAbivN","text_ar":"خَابِثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (K:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an adulterer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fornicator:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a blamer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"censurer:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a slanderer,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"calumniator:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 611:) [and, applied to a venomous reptile and the like,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"malignant,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noxious;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as well as"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"impure, unclean, foul,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"filthy:"},{"kind":"text","text":"] the fem. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvapN","text_ar":"خَبِيثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Msb:) the pl. masc. is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibaAvN","text_ar":"خِبَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubuvN","text_ar":"خُبُثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", for which it is allowable to say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubovN","text_ar":"خُبْثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", accord. to the dial. of Temeem, (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubavaA='u","text_ar":"خُبَثَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, Msb, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$urafaA='u","text_ar":"شُرَفَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyfN","text_ar":"شَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Msb,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axobaAvN","text_ar":"اَخْبَاثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^a$araAfN","text_ar":"اَشَرَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[another pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ariyfN","text_ar":"شَرِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], (Msb, MF, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabavapN","text_ar":"خَبَثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Kr, Msb, MF, TA,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEafapN","text_ar":"ضَعَفَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"DaEiyfN","text_ar":"ضَعِيفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, MF, TA,) two instances of which the like can scarcely be found, (Msb,) or is not found among sound words, for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saraApN","text_ar":"سَرَاةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sariY~N","text_ar":"سَرِىٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is an unsound word, (MF, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xubuwvN","text_ar":"خُبُوثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AZ, TA,) which is also extr., (TA,) [and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaAvaY","text_ar":"خَبَاثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HazaAnaY","text_ar":"حَزَانَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaziynN","text_ar":"حَزِينٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":",) applied in the A, in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xnv","text_ar":"خنث"},{"kind":"text","text":", to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xanaAvaY","text_ar":"خَنَاثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xunovaY","text_ar":"خُنْثَى"},{"kind":"text","text":",] and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvuwna","text_ar":"خَبِيثُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[applied only to rational beings]: (Mgh:) and the pl. fem., i. e. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvapN","text_ar":"خَبِيثَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaAy^ivu","text_ar":"خَبَايِثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvaAtN","text_ar":"خَبِيثَاتٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al$~ajarapu","text_ar":"الشَّجَرَةُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxabiyvapu","text_ar":"الخَبِيثَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", mentioned in the Kur [xiv. 31], (TA,) means"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The colocynth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ka$uwv","text_ar":"كَشُوث"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K; TA,) which is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain plant that clings to the branches of trees and has no root in the earth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S and K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k$v","text_ar":"كشث"},{"kind":"text","text":";) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of cuscuta,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dodder;"},{"kind":"text","text":"] or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yellow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Euruwq","text_ar":"عُرُوق"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that cling to trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA in the present art.:) also occurring in a trad., as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the garlic-plant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the onion;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the leek;"},{"kind":"text","text":"because of their disagreeable taste and odour. (IAth, TA.) It is said in a trad. respecting the slain at Bedr, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^uloquwA fiY qaliybK xabiyvK muxobivK","text_ar":"اُلْقُوا فِى قَلِيبٍ خَبِيثٍ مُخْبِثٍ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They were cast into a well corrupt, and corrupting"},{"kind":"text","text":"what fell into it. (TA.) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvN muxobivN","text_ar":"خَبِيثٌ مُخْبِثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvN","text_ar":"خَبِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muxobivN","text_ar":"مُخْبِثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xaAbivN","text_ar":"خَابِثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobavaAnN","text_ar":"مَخْبَثَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, L, K,) applied to a man, signify One"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"who takes to himself bad, wicked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful, companions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"friends"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, L, K, TA) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"connexions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistants:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobavaAnu","text_ar":"مَخْبَثَانُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", as a determinate noun, [without the article"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Al","text_ar":"ال"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is only used in calling to, or addressing, a person: (K:) you say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA maxobavaAnu","text_ar":"يَا مَخْبَثَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) fem. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobavaAnapu","text_ar":"مَخْبَثَانَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": and to a man and woman together,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA maxobavaAnu","text_ar":"يا مَخْبَثَانُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) and in the phrase ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvN muxobivN","text_ar":"خَبِيثٌ مُخْبِثٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", the former word signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad, wicked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful, in himself;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having bad, wicked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful, companions"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"friends"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"assistants."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, TA.) One says also, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAxubavu","text_ar":"يَاخُبَثُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA xabiyvu","text_ar":"يا خَبِيثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful"},{"kind":"text","text":"man!]; and to a woman, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAxabaAvi","text_ar":"يَاخَبَاثِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) indecl., with kesr for its termination, (S,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA xabiyvapu","text_ar":"يا خَبِيثَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K [accord. to SM: so in all the copies in his hands; but not found by him in any other lexicon: not in the CK, nor in my MS. copy of the K.]) ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabaAvi","text_ar":"خَبَاثِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"also occurs, in a saying of El-Hasan, addressed to the present world,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~unoyaA","text_ar":"الدُّنْيَا"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaA xibovapu","text_ar":"يَا خِبْثَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"was said by El-Hajjáj to Anas, as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA xabiyvu","text_ar":"يا خَبِيثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": and is also used as meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thou of"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bad, wicked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful, qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispositions!"},{"kind":"text","text":"[app. addressed to a woman, as the context seems to show; and agreeably with an assertion in Ham p. 810, that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xibovpN","text_ar":"خِبْثةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is sometimes used in speaking of an old woman]. (L, TA.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvu Aln~afosi","text_ar":"خَبِيثُ النَّفْسِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Having the soul"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stomach"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heavy,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"heaving,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"agitated by a tendency to vomit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and in a disagreeable state."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maxobavaAnN","text_ar":"مَخْبَثَانٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a lie occurs in a trad, as meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xabiyvN","text_ar":"خَبِيثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"app. in an intensive sense [i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Very abominable"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (TA.) In the saying,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEuwdu biA@ll~`hi","text_ar":"اَعُودُ بِا@للّٰهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aall~`hum~a A_in~iY A^aEuwdu bika","text_ar":"اَللّٰهُمَّ اـِنِّى اَعُودُ بِكَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, * K, * TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alxubuvi waAlxbaAy^ivi","text_ar":"مِنَ الخُبُثِ وَالخبَايِثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, TA,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waAlxabaAy^ivi","text_ar":"وَالخَبَايِثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mina Alxubovi","text_ar":"مِنَ الخُبْثِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Msb, K, TA,) a form of words which Mohammad directed his followers to pronounce on entering a privy, or place of retirement for the relief of nature, because devils are in such a place, (Mgh, TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxubuv","text_ar":"الخُبُث"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxabiyv","text_ar":"الخَبِيث"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh, Msb, TA,) and so is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxubov","text_ar":"الخُبْث"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the dial. of Temeem, (Msb, TA,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxabaAy^iv","text_ar":"الخَبَايِث"},{"kind":"text","text":"is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxabiyvap","text_ar":"الخَبِيثَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Mgh, TA;;) and the meaning is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I seek protection by God,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"O God, I seek protection by Thee, from the male devils and the female devils,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Mgh, Msb, K, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the genii and of mankind:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh:) or, reading ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxubov","text_ar":"الخُبْث","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [as a subst,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from infidelity and the devils:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Bekr, TA:) or, [so reading, and regarding"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlxbAy^v","text_ar":"الخبايث"},{"kind":"text","text":"as pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxabiyvapu","text_ar":"الخَبِيثَةُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"used as a subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from infidelity and acts of disobedience:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) or,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"from wicked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"unrighteous, conduct, such as adultery and the like, and culpable actions and evil qualities"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dispositions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"El-Khattábee asserts that the reading"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxubov","text_ar":"الخُبْث"},{"kind":"text","text":", with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"b","text_ar":"ب"},{"kind":"text","text":"quiescent, is a mistake of the relaters of traditions; but En-Nawawee rejects this assertion. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","Msb","Mgh","IAth","A","K","S","MF","Kr","AZ","L"]},{"entry_id":"n9877","headword_ar":"خِبِّيثٌ","root":"xbv","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", applied to a man, (TA,) signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kaviyru","text_ar":"كَثِيرُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alxubovi","text_ar":"الخُبْثِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Very bad"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"deceitful;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"much addicted to adultery"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fornication"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xib~iyvuwna","text_ar":"خِبِّيثُونَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)"}],"source_refs":["TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}